============================================================================
DIAGNOSTIC INTERPRETATION
============================================================================

What PASSED (5):
  - sm_smoke / sandbox     M1+M2 musl libbinder + servicemanager round-trip
  - HelloBinder            M3 dalvikvm ServiceManager listServices/getService
  - AsInterfaceTest        M3++ same-process Stub.asInterface elision
  - BCP-shim               PF-arch-053 (slim shim on -Xbootclasspath)
  - BCP-framework          PF-arch-053 (framework.jar + ext.jar on BCP)

  This is the canonical "M1-M3+ regression set". All five verify the
  binder pivot's foundational layer: libbinder protocol, servicemanager,
  Java JNI plumbing, framework.jar bootclasspath sanity. They all pass on
  a freshly-rebooted phone — the binder substrate is solid.

What FAILED (7):
  All 7 M4 service tests (ActivityServiceTest, PowerServiceTest,
  SystemServiceRouteTest, DisplayServiceTest, NotificationServiceTest,
  InputMethodServiceTest, WindowServiceTest) fail with the same Parcel
  header mismatch:

    Parcel: Expecting header 0x53595354 but found 0x564e4452.
            Mixing copies of libbinder?

  0x53595354 = 'SYST' — Phase 1 setting per
                        patches/0003-parcel-kheader-syst.patch (default
                        per README §"patches/0003-parcel-kheader-syst.patch")
  0x564e4452 = 'VNDR' — Phase 2 production OHOS-vendor binder endpoint

  The 'Mixing copies of libbinder?' message is libbinder's own diagnostic
  for exactly this case: two endpoints on /dev/vndbinder where one was
  built with WESTLAKE_KHEADER_VNDR=1 and the other with WESTLAKE_KHEADER_SYST=1.

  Hypothesis (NOT verified — out of scope for D2): something in the recent
  M4-PRE7/M4-PRE8/M4-PRE9/M5-PRE work that grew dalvikvm's link-time
  libbinder_full_static.a may have flipped to VNDR while the freshly-
  restarted vndservicemanager (still using out/bionic/libbinder.so built
  for Phase 1) speaks SYST. The m3-dalvikvm-boot.sh kicks off a fresh SM
  each test, so SM speaks SYST; dalvikvm client speaks VNDR; mismatch.

  All 7 FAILs are identical in shape, consistent with a single root cause
  (the SYST/VNDR mismatch), not 7 independent service bugs. This is
  exactly the kind of regression the suite is designed to surface — its
  cause should be investigated by the relevant agent (audit dalvikvm
  link config vs out/bionic/libbinder.so build flag).

  NOTE: Tests #2-#5 (HelloBinder etc.) all PASS — they ALSO use libbinder
  but apparently don't trigger the mismatch path (perhaps the JNI bridge
  short-circuit on local services skips the Parcel header check?). That
  the same dalvikvm + same SM produces PASS for M3-era tests and FAIL for
  M4-era tests means whatever the new tests do *differently* (likely
  ServiceRegistrar's addService loop, which exercises the cross-process
  marshal path more aggressively than M3 tests) is exposing the mismatch.

What SKIPPED (1):
  - noice-discover         out of scope for --quick mode (by design)

